Mr. Jack Lynch is responsible for all patent filings and the overall intellectual property strategy for the Company.Mr. Lynch has over 50 years experience in practice before the U.S. District and Appellate courts and the U.S. Patent and Trademark Office.  His Juris Doctor is from Georgetown Law School and he holds a BS in chemistry from Fordham University.  Mr. Lynch was the founding partner in a New York City law firm, which merged with Fulbright & Jaworski in 1998.  He has taught IP law courses since 1997 at Georgetown, the University of San Francisco School of Law  (as well as summer sessions at Trinity University in Dublin and Charles University in Prague) and Ave Maria School of Law.







      
